<title>UK: Severn Trent buys back 18 mln shares.</title>
<headline>Severn Trent buys back 18 mln shares.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-12-17</dateline>
<text>
<p>British water company Severn Trent plc said on Tuesday it had instructed HSBC James Capel and UBS Ltd as its agents to buy back up to 18 million of its shares, representing five percent of the group's issued share capital.</p>
<p>The announcement follows the announcement on November 26 that severn Trent intended to buyback 10 percent of its shares.</p>
<p>In early trading, Severn Trent shares were 15p higher at 669p.</p>
